### Question 8
Create a query to display the total number of employees and, of that total, the number of
employees hired in 1980, 1981, and 1982. Create appropriate column headings.

**SQL Command:**
```sql
select count(*) as "Total Employees",
       count(case when to_char(hire_date,'YYYY') = '1980' then 1 end) as "Hired 1980",
       count(case when to_char(hire_date,'YYYY') = '1981' then 1 end) as "Hired 1981",
       count(case when to_char(hire_date,'YYYY') = '1982' then 1 end) as "Hired 1982"
from hr.employees;
```